# Cursor Rules for Real-time AI Chatbot

## Project Context
Real-time AI chatbot with WebSocket communication, intent recognition, and smart response generation for customer support.

## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, Socket.IO
- **AI/ML**: Custom NLP intent classification
- **Database**: MongoDB (optional)
- **Package Manager**: npm

## Code Style
- Use ES6+ JavaScript
- Follow async/await pattern
- Use camelCase for variables
- Add comments for intent recognition logic

## File Structure
```
/
├── server.js
├── routes/
├── services/
│   ├── intentRecognizer.js
│   └── responseGenerator.js
├── models/
└── socket/
    └── chatHandler.js
```

## AI/ML Guidelines
- Implement intent recognition in separate service
- Document intent patterns clearly
- Handle context in conversations
- Optimize for real-time performance
- Test with various query types

## WebSocket Development
- Use Socket.IO for real-time communication
- Handle connection/disconnection events
- Implement message queuing
- Manage session state
- Handle errors gracefully

## Security
- Validate all user inputs
- Rate limit connections
- Use secure WebSocket (WSS)
- Protect against injection attacks
- Encrypt sensitive data

## Performance
- Optimize message processing
- Cache common responses
- Handle concurrent connections
- Monitor connection health
- Implement reconnection logic

